00:48:03.230 --> 00:48:04.330
How could she be dead?

00:48:04.330 --> 00:48:05.080
I'm so distraught!

00:48:05.080 --> 00:48:05.820
And there it is.

00:48:05.820 --> 00:48:06.570
Ah!

00:48:06.570 --> 00:48:08.034
I forgot to change its water.

00:48:08.034 --> 00:48:09.450
Doesn't matter
everything else you

00:48:09.450 --> 00:48:10.270
do-- if you don't
change its water,

00:48:10.270 --> 00:48:11.610
the goldfish is going to die.

00:48:11.610 --> 00:48:13.560
So the point is--
what's the point?

00:48:13.560 --> 00:48:16.674
The point is, if we care
about the core definition

00:48:16.674 --> 00:48:18.840
of epidemiology, understanding
the causes of health,

00:48:18.840 --> 00:48:20.784
the causes of
health are complex.

00:48:20.784 --> 00:48:22.200
The causes of
health ultimately do

00:48:22.200 --> 00:48:23.820
involve the water, as well
as the fish's behavior,

00:48:23.820 --> 00:48:25.260
as well as the fish's genome.

00:48:25.260 --> 00:48:25.980
Going to to Blind
Willie Johnson,

00:48:25.980 --> 00:48:27.050
we need to care
about the malaria,

00:48:27.050 --> 00:48:28.030
we need to care
about homelessness,

00:48:28.030 --> 00:48:30.113
care about racism, we need
to care about violence.

00:48:30.113 --> 00:48:31.935
And unfortunately,
unfortunately, I

00:48:31.935 --> 00:48:34.350
am here to tell you that
there is no magic bullet.

00:48:34.350 --> 00:48:36.450
And the reason why
American health indicators

00:48:36.450 --> 00:48:37.890
have been as bad
as they have been

00:48:37.890 --> 00:48:40.410
is because we have focused
on only one aspect of this.

00:48:40.410 --> 00:48:43.410
That if we are serious
about improving health,

00:48:43.410 --> 00:48:46.170
we need to take epidemiology
to its core definition,

00:48:46.170 --> 00:48:48.660
understand the full range
of complex causes of health,

00:48:48.660 --> 00:48:50.452
and work on all of
them at the same time.

